# This is an example Python programme which calculates the total cost for a user's
# holiday, using input values and options for: plane cost, hotel cost, and car rental cost.
# The programme is compatible with different input options.

# User inputs ------------------------------------------------------
# city_flight: The city they will be flying to. (each city has a different flight costs)
# num_nights: The number of nights they will be staying at a hotel
# rental_days: The number of days that they will be hiring a car for.

# Functions --------------------------------------------------------
# hotel_cost: This function takes num_nights as an argument, and 
# returns a total cost for the hotel stay.

# plane_cost: This function takes city_flight as an argument and
# returns a cost for the flight (if/else if statements used to retrieve a price based on the chosen city)

# car_rental: his function takes rental_days as an argument and 
# returns the total cost of the car rental (based on daily rental cost.)

